<p>Below are the configuration options for Bitbucket for use on your Probo Open Source server. There are configurations for both the docker-compose.yml file and the bitbucket-handler.yml file. Use the one that is most applicable to your server setup.</p>

<h4>Bitbucket Handler For Open Source Server YAML: bitbucket-handler.yml</h4>
<div class="probo-monospace">
bbClientKey: '{{ client_key }}'<br />
bbClientSecret: '{{ client_secret }}'<br />
bbAccessToken: '{{ access_token }}'<br />
bbRefreshToken: '{{ refresh_token }}'
</div>

<h4>Probo Open Source Server docker-compose.yml Configuration</h4>
<div class="probo-monospace">
BB_CLIENT_KEY: {{ client_key  }}<br />
BB_CLIENT_SECRET: {{ client_secret }}<br />
BB_ACCESS_TOKEN: {{ access_token }}<br />
BB_REFRESH_TOKEN: {{ refresh_token }}
</div>
